        "created_at": "2025-07-13T19:58:56.274Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I searched and did not see this requested to date. So here it goes: I would ask for a feature that could be adjusted in settings, that gives you a UX dialog box warning you before joining or posting in any Signal conversation or group chat that does not have disappearing messages on. And that gives you a visual of what the current disappearing messages times are set for.</p>\n<p>Goal: to make it so if your policy is to always have disappearing messages on all your conversations, that you do not accidentially join in conversations that are not so.</p>",
