        "created_at": "2025-07-13T20:22:55.369Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I thought the group key was only involved in group management e.g. joins, leaves etc., not content management.</p>\n<p>Edit: <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/pdfs/signal_private_group_system.pdf?utm_source=perplexity\">This white paper</a> confirms what I thought; disappearing messages settings are indeed invisible to the server:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Design Goals\tPrivacy of group membership and metadata\tp. 2‚Äì3</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>System Overview\tEncrypted storage of group data on the server\tp. 3‚Äì5</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Security Properties\tServer blindness to group membership and settings\tp. 8‚Äì9</p>\n</li>\n</ol>",
