        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/{size}/31625_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-14T07:49:23.473Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Avitus\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"70409\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/avitus/48/34172_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Avitus:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>invisible to the server</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>again, invisible to the server and invisible to the client are two different things, but i get that it seems you can‚Äôt get the disappearing message info before joining.<br>\ni still think this is a client solution and not a server solution, but it means it‚Äôs somewhat a clunky solution since it requires you to essentially join in to the group, only then get the warning with the option of leaving.</p>",
