        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/n/9f8e36/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-14T11:29:22.515Z",
        "cooked": "<p>For what it‚Äôs worth, I think the client should be able to know this information from an invite? You can see group data like member count, group name, and group icon, so I see no reason the client <em>couldn‚Äôt</em> have this information available pre-joining.</p>\n<p>Like, even if the group data is shielded from the server, the client still can access it (and <em>necessarily</em> has to) to be able to accept the invite.</p>\n<p>It‚Äôs always possible that this information just isn‚Äôt given to the client before joining, but I see no obvious reason why this would be the case.</p>",
