        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-top_contributors\" data-username=\"rassilon1963\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"70409\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/48/31625_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> rassilon1963:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>invisible to the server and invisible to the client are two different things</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I know the difference <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slightly_smiling_face.png?v=12\" title=\":slightly_smiling_face:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slightly_smiling_face:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\">.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-top_contributors\" data-username=\"rassilon1963\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"70409\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/48/31625_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> rassilon1963:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>but i get that it seems you can‚Äôt get the disappearing message info before joining.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I keep emphasizing that the <em><strong>server</strong></em> doesn‚Äôt know because it would need to know to then tell you what a group‚Äôs disappearing messages settings are <em><strong>before</strong></em> joining a group, which is the feature request. So, again, I don‚Äôt think this is possible without a fundamental change to what the server can see; otherwise:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote group-top_contributors quote-modified\" data-username=\"rassilon1963\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"70409\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/rassilon1963/48/31625_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> rassilon1963:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>client solution means it‚Äôs somewhat a clunky solution since it requires you to essentially join in to the group, only then get the warning with the option of leaving.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/slightly_smiling_face.png?v=12\" title=\":slightly_smiling_face:\" class=\"emoji only-emoji\" alt=\":slightly_smiling_face:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
